> [{quoted}](name=Meddler,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=KbiAXyB8,comment-id=0025,timestamp=2016-01-07T04:39:58.065+0000)
>
> Yeah, Ohmwrecker's still in a pretty sad spot. We did try out some stuff during the preseason development period to try and make it more interesting in its niche, with tower sieging still being its core. The most interesting approach, that alas didn't end up working very well, was a version of it that replaced your auto attacks against towers with a ranged channel that dealt ramping damage over time. Gave melee champs a way to contribute siege damage without having to hard commit basically. Was fun to play around with, but hard to justify taking over other options, even on the characters it was theoretically designed for. 
> 
> At some point we will take another look at Ohmwrecker, though I suspect if it doesn't work out next time we'll probably end up cutting it. Making it less situational, while keeping it tower focused still, could be a reasonable approach, and an allied tower interaction sounds worth a try as a result.

Speaking of Which
how do you feel about
{{item:1083}} 
{{item:3512}} 
{{item:3504}} 
{{item:3091}} 


Theyre Items that have been around for a while yet have pretty low build rates.

Personally I love all of them and I dont want them simply removed but I do think they could use a small buff

Turn it into a modified {{summoner:17}} 
"Allied Turret: Grant massive regeneration for 4 seconds
Enemy turret: Disable basic attacks for 3 seconds"

They had something like that on the pbe a long time ago, it was like "If used next to allied turrets, increases the turrets damage by X amount for 3-4 seconds" And I believe the X was 100% but not to sure on it. Honestly...the item isn't even that bad stat wise, it gives cdr, and a good amount of health regen and even more armor than sunfire cape for about the same cost.

But yea if you don't plan on getting as your first or 2nd item, than it usually isn't worth getting. I think the item would see more play if they maybe give it another 100 hp, because while it's stats is decent...to make it more useful you need to buy it early and 300 hp is kind of low for a first/second buy tank item, at least at 400 hp you could feel like it's a little bit more for tanks.

I could see this item being good for tanks who are aggressive and would like to dive, also champions who also like health regen. {{champion:36}} {{champion:86}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:154}}
